    <item>
      <title>Setting Up Hugo on Cloudflare</title>
      <link>https://jnicholson.blog/2022/05/27/setting-up-hugo-on-cloudflare.html</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 27 May 2022 22:31:19 -0400</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://jnicholson.micro.blog/2022/05/28/setting-up-hugo-on-cloudflare.html</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I wanted to start off by sharing how I set up this my original homepage. I was impressed by how easy it was to do, especially since I&amp;rsquo;m new to both Hugo and Cloudflare Pages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I followed the &lt;a href=&#34;https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/framework-guides/deploy-a-hugo-site/&#34;&gt;excellent documentation&lt;/a&gt; that Cloudflare provides. If you&amp;rsquo;re not married to the idea of using Hugo, they also provide great documentation on &lt;a href=&#34;https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/framework-guides/&#34;&gt;other frameworks&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One thing I missed the first time I pushed updates to my repo was &lt;a href=&#34;https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/framework-guides/deploy-a-hugo-site/#using-a-specific-hugo-version&#34;&gt;setting the version of Hugo&lt;/a&gt;. The version that Hugo provides is older and didn&amp;rsquo;t work with my chosen theme.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
